# Project

- Follow [AGENTS.md](mdc:AGENTS.md) for env, commands, and conventions.
- Prefer existing `wikipedia/` patterns when adding models or scripts.
- Keep changes scoped to what was asked.
- When the user invokes `/concise` or asks to be concise / keep it short / trim it down / cut the fluff / TL;DR (including implicit brevity), read and follow `.cursor/skills/concise/SKILL.md` (compose with any other active skill).
- When writing, editing, refactoring, or reviewing Python/PyTorch (including implicit `.py` work, or `/python-coding`), read and follow `.cursor/skills/python-coding/SKILL.md`.
- When working on ML/DL code — model architectures, datasets/dataloaders, tokenizers, training, checkpointing, inference, or model configs (including implicit ML work, or `/ml-coding`) — read and follow `.cursor/skills/ml-coding/SKILL.md` (compose with `python-coding`).
